<%
// Tree Removal Service Page
%>

<!-- Page Header -->
<section class="page-header" style="background-image: url('/images/tree-removal.jpg');">
    <div class="overlay"></div>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Tree Removal Services in Gold Beach, OR</h1>
        <p>Safe & Professional Tree Removal on the Southern Oregon Coast</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Main Content -->
<section class="service-detail section-padding">
    <div class="container">
        
        <!-- Introduction with Image -->
        <div class="service-intro">
            <div class="intro-text">
                <p>JT & Sons Tree Service LLC provides safe, professional tree removal services in Gold Beach, Oregon and surrounding areas including Brookings, Pistol River, Ophir, Agnes, Port Orford, Sixes, Langlois, Bandon, and Coos Bay.</p>
                <p>With over 30 years of experience, our family-owned company specializes in removing hazardous, damaged, dead, or unwanted trees while protecting your property. Trees along the Southern Oregon Coast often face strong winds, heavy rain, and storm damage. When a tree becomes unstable, diseased, or too close to structures or power lines, professional removal is the safest solution.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="intro-image">
                <img src="/images/tree-romove1.jpg" alt="Tree Removal Service" class="rounded-image">
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Signs You May Need Tree Removal -->
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Signs You May Need Tree Removal</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Dead or Dying Trees</strong> – Dead trees can quickly become hazardous and may fall without warning, especially during coastal storms.</li>
                <li><strong>Storm-Damaged Trees</strong> – High winds and storms can weaken trees or break large limbs. If a tree has been severely damaged, removal may be required.</li>
                <li><strong>Leaning or Structurally Unstable Trees</strong> – Trees that lean significantly or show signs of root damage can pose a serious danger.</li>
                <li><strong>Trees Too Close to Structures or Power Lines</strong> – Trees growing too close to homes, buildings, or power lines should be professionally managed.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Process + Image Row -->
        <div class="service-include-row">
            <div class="service-list">
                <h2>Our Tree Removal Process</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Tree Inspection & Assessment</strong> – Our team carefully evaluates the tree's condition, location, and surrounding environment to determine the safest removal method.</li>
                    <li><strong>Safe Tree Removal</strong> – Using professional equipment and controlled cutting techniques, we safely remove the tree in sections when necessary to prevent damage to nearby structures.</li>
                    <li><strong>Debris Removal & Cleanup</strong> – After the tree is removed, we clear away branches, logs, and debris to leave your property clean and organized.</li>
                    <li><strong>Additional Tree Care Services</strong> – If needed, we can also provide stump grinding, brush removal, and fire reduction services to fully restore your landscape.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="service-image">
                <img src="/images/coos-bay.jpg" alt="Tree Removal Process" class="rounded-image">
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Service Areas -->
        <div class="content-container">
            <h2>Tree Removal Services Across the Southern Oregon Coast</h2>
            <p>JT & Sons Tree Service LLC proudly provides professional tree removal services in: Gold Beach, Brookings, Pistol River, Ophir, Agness, Port Orford, Sixes, Langlois, Bandon, and Coos Bay.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact Info Box -->
        <div class="contact-info-box">
            <h3>Get a Free Tree Removal Estimate</h3>
            <p>
                <i class="fas fa-phone-alt"></i> Office: <a href="tel:<%= sitePhone %>"><%= sitePhone %></a><br>
                <i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i> Cell/Text: <a href="tel:<%= siteCell %>"><%= siteCell %></a><br>
                <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Email: <a href="mailto:<%= siteEmail %>"><%= siteEmail %></a>
            </p>
            <p>Contact us today to schedule your free estimate.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>